			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="1">
				And Elihu answered and said:
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035002">
			</marker>
			<begin-block-indent
				>
			</begin-block-indent>
			<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="2">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Do you think this to be just?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				Do you say, 
				<crossref let="v" cid="c18035002.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				It is my right before God,
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035003">
			</marker>
			<verse num="3">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				that you ask, 
				<crossref let="w" cid="c18035003.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				What advantage have I?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				How am I better off than if I had sinned?
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035004">
			</marker>
			<verse num="4">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				I will answer you
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and 
				<crossref let="x" cid="c18035004.1">
				</crossref>
				your friends with you.
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035005">
			</marker>
			<verse num="5">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="y" cid="c18035005.1">
				</crossref>
				Look at the heavens, and see;
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and behold the clouds, which are higher than you.
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035006">
			</marker>
			<verse num="6">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				If you have sinned, 
				<crossref let="z" cid="c18035006.1">
				</crossref>
				what do you accomplish against him?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				And if your transgressions are multiplied, what do you do to him?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035007">
			</marker>
			<verse num="7">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="a" cid="c18035007.1">
				</crossref>
				If you are righteous, what do you give to him?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				Or what does he receive from your hand?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035008">
			</marker>
			<verse num="8">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				Your wickedness concerns a man like yourself,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and your righteousness 
				<crossref let="b" cid="c18035008.1">
				</crossref>
				a son of man.
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v18035009">
			</marker>
